<!-- custom: note 3: filename needs to be hardcoded in the DLL it seems in CvXMLLoadUtilitySet.cpp which i already did (so no need to change anything if you just want to use this file to tweak SAS settings anyways etc) for current filename GlobalDefines_advciv_sas.xml, but if you want to change this file's name or/and add other global define files, make sure they are added there as well if i am not mistaken and chatgpt 5 confirms it, or it won't load as it didn't seem to (load anyways etc) before i added the filename there (but no change needed if you just want to use the file with this filename to tweak settings, it's only info for modding/modders anyways etc), check to be sure anyways etc -->

<Civ4Defines xmlns="x-schema:CIV4GlobalDefinesSchema.xml">

	<!-- custom: very bad tiles management knobs in AIFoundValue::evaluate function. Tweaking these allows to change the code we added that tells AI how very bad tiles are valued. Changing it will (at least should but anyways etc) change AI settling preferences and recommended sites in UI as well if i'm not mistaken anyways etc. Are accounted as very bad tiles (check if not updated in code anyways etc), in BFC (excluding home plot (i.e. plot where we settle/found/plant our city anyways etc)):
		- peak tiles
		- ice cap tiles
		- desert tiles that are not hill and have no bonus
		- snow (i.e. ice sheet) tiles that are not hill and have no bonus
	Start phase is before our first city is planted/settled/founded but anyways etc.
	-->
	<Define>
		<DefineName>SAS_EVALUATE_MAX_TOLERATED_NOT_HOME_VERY_BAD_TILES_START</DefineName>
		<iDefineIntVal>2</iDefineIntVal>
	</Define>
	<Define>
		<DefineName>SAS_EVALUATE_MAX_TOLERATED_NOT_HOME_VERY_BAD_TILES_LATER</DefineName>
		<iDefineIntVal>3</iDefineIntVal>
	</Define>
	<!-- custom: the higher this positive number is, the more we penalize and think this tile is very very bad, for example 75 would mean a harsher evaluation of this tile and thus likeliness to avoid the city site that has this tile in BFC than say 50 if i'm not mistaken but anyways etc. This value is multiplied by the number of bad tiles if we are past the max tolerated threshold, for example if we have 4 very bad tiles in BFC and we are at start game and the start very bad base value is 100, the currently evaluated city site that has these in BFC would have a penalty in value (and thus likeliness to consider it our best site to settle) of 4 * 100 = - 400 to its value which is as of now a bit more than what iron would give for example so quite big but anyways etc. -->
	<Define>
		<DefineName>SAS_EVALUATE_VALUE_NOT_HOME_VERY_BAD_TILE_START</DefineName>
		<iDefineIntVal>75</iDefineIntVal>
	</Define>
	<Define>
		<DefineName>SAS_EVALUATE_VALUE_NOT_HOME_VERY_BAD_TILE_LATER</DefineName>
		<iDefineIntVal>25</iDefineIntVal>
	</Define>
</Civ4Defines>
